Context:
At Capital One, Card Tech was facing delivery bottlenecks, low velocity, and siloed development across multiple teams.

Role & Leadership:
As Senior Technology Delivery Manager, I led the horizontal agile transformation across SAFe trains to improve predictability and transparency.

Initiatives:
	•	Introduced lean intake, refinement workflows, and backlog grooming practices
	•	Designed a capacity planning model to estimate realistic delivery timelines
	•	Conducted coaching sessions with Product Owners and Scrum Masters

Outcome:
	•	Achieved <45-day feature cycle time
	•	Reduced sprint carryover by 40%
	•	Streamlined program increment planning and improved stakeholder trust
